WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:10.000
[English subtitles are available]

00:38.820 --> 00:40.650
Dad, dad, are you okay?

00:40.650 --> 00:41.990
The other hospital also refused us.

00:41.990 --> 00:43.990
Then where can we go?

00:43.990 --> 00:45.120
I'm begging you, please help him.

00:45.120 --> 00:47.590
We have nowhere to call.

00:47.590 --> 00:51.160
No, no.

00:51.160 --> 00:54.530
Dad, dad.

00:54.530 --> 01:00.510
When people live, there will be a sudden instant,

01:00.510 --> 01:02.510
Dad.

01:02.510 --> 01:05.180
Dad.

01:05.180 --> 01:08.250
Dad. Dad.

01:10.380 --> 01:14.490
where they search for God so badly.

01:16.920 --> 01:19.660
Damn it.

01:20.930 --> 01:23.200
It's the abdominal arteriorrhexis patient who just called you.

01:23.200 --> 01:24.630
We don't have a doctor who can do the operation.

01:24.630 --> 01:26.000
Didn't I just tell you that?

01:26.000 --> 01:28.270
What can we do when they insist to come?

01:28.270 --> 01:29.530
He's in the state of hypovolemic shock.

01:29.530 --> 01:31.300
Now it's hard to maintain vital signs.

01:31.300 --> 01:32.900
He'll die if he doesn't receive treatment immediately.

01:32.900 --> 01:35.370
We can't do the treatment, please hurry and leave.

01:35.410 --> 01:37.880
Hurry.

01:38.240 --> 01:38.740
Doctor Ha?

01:38.740 --> 01:40.580
Yes.

01:40.580 --> 01:41.610
Let's go.

01:41.610 --> 01:43.180
Doctor.

01:43.180 --> 01:45.720
Please save my father.

01:45.720 --> 01:48.590
I'm begging you, please.

01:49.720 --> 01:51.160
Send them away.

01:52.720 --> 01:55.229
If God is too busy to help,

01:55.229 --> 01:59.330
there is a slight hope that even if it's a ghost, he could help.

01:59.330 --> 02:00.400
We are sending him out.

02:00.400 --> 02:00.930
No!

02:00.930 --> 02:03.440
Don't do that!

02:08.710 --> 02:10.509
Please reconsider.

02:10.509 --> 02:11.940
If we send the patient away like this,

02:11.940 --> 02:13.950
he might die on the way.

02:13.950 --> 02:15.650
Are you crazy?

02:15.650 --> 02:17.280
You are just an intern, how dare you to speak up like this?

02:17.280 --> 02:18.750
Hurry up and send him away, what are you waiting for?

02:18.750 --> 02:21.350
No!

02:21.790 --> 02:24.620
Wait a minute.

02:27.530 --> 02:29.160
Isn't this a hospital?

02:29.160 --> 02:30.560
Aren't we doctors?

02:30.560 --> 02:31.600
If doctors abandon patients,

02:31.600 --> 02:32.260
then who will...

02:32.260 --> 02:34.500
You fool, still think you are a doctor.

02:34.500 --> 02:40.070
Hey, then will you do the treatment for him?

02:53.350 --> 02:57.120
Dad, no!

03:12.470 --> 03:14.270
[Ghost Doctor]

03:14.070 --> 03:15.810
Then what happened?

03:15.810 --> 03:19.540
Did the ghost save the uncle's patient?

03:18.310 --> 03:20.910
[Episode 1]

03:19.540 --> 03:20.350
You are curious.

03:20.350 --> 03:22.579
Then...

03:22.579 --> 03:24.079
It's a secret.

03:24.079 --> 03:25.480
If people in the world know it,

03:25.480 --> 03:26.890
something big is going to happen.

03:26.890 --> 03:29.520
Do that kind of ghosts really exist?

03:29.520 --> 03:32.960
Of course, they should be here, in the hospital, too.

03:32.960 --> 03:35.260
The patron saint who guards the sick.

03:35.260 --> 03:36.760
Do you know what a patron saint is?

03:36.760 --> 03:39.060
So my little patients,

03:39.060 --> 03:42.670
remember that there is always a ghost doctor by your side,

03:42.670 --> 03:44.170
and you should thank them.

03:44.170 --> 03:45.170
Say thank you to them.

03:45.170 --> 03:46.970
You lied.

03:46.970 --> 03:50.380
How can there be such kind ghosts?

03:50.380 --> 03:51.480
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

03:51.480 --> 03:52.610
- You lied.
- You lied.

03:52.610 --> 03:54.550
How can a doctor turn into a ghost?

03:54.550 --> 03:56.410
Is a ghost a superhero?

03:56.410 --> 03:58.020
She is lying, a big lie.

03:58.020 --> 03:58.880
Let's go.

03:58.880 --> 04:01.190
The children now are really stubborn.

04:01.190 --> 04:04.560
They don't listen to the grown-ups.

04:10.160 --> 04:13.870
If we can solve it by living being's power,

04:12.960 --> 04:16.300
[12 years later]

04:16.300 --> 04:20.339
then it's a lie, a big lie.

04:26.380 --> 04:29.750
[EMC, EunSang University Medical Center]

04:29.750 --> 04:32.750
[Medical Center]

04:36.250 --> 04:38.120
Gorgeous.

04:38.120 --> 04:42.930
He doesn't let us down today either.

04:43.760 --> 04:46.030
That's Professor Cha Yeong Min of Thoracic Surgery.

04:46.030 --> 04:47.570
What? He's a professor?

04:47.570 --> 04:49.670
Right, you are surprised, too.

04:49.670 --> 04:51.370
With that appearance and that figure,

04:51.370 --> 04:53.440
why does he become a doctor?

04:53.440 --> 04:57.880
Except that, he's mysterious, too.

04:57.880 --> 05:00.610
What's the matter?

05:02.150 --> 05:04.920
So, when did you do the CPR?

05:12.160 --> 05:13.790
It took us about 30 minutes to get here.

05:13.790 --> 05:14.330
For no witness,

05:14.330 --> 05:15.560
we can't know for sure when the heart stopped beating.

05:15.560 --> 05:18.760
Please go this way.

05:30.380 --> 05:31.140
Let Doctor An go.

05:31.140 --> 05:33.810
ECMO is not needed.

05:37.650 --> 05:40.690
Please step aside.

05:44.860 --> 05:46.690
Okay, 1, 2, 3.

05:47.130 --> 05:49.130
Measure the blood pressure.

05:51.230 --> 05:52.960
Inhale.

05:55.970 --> 05:57.740
7.5 milliliter.

05:59.470 --> 06:00.910
Let me do this.

06:03.840 --> 06:05.240
Parrot pose.

06:08.750 --> 06:10.080
Pneumothorax.

06:10.080 --> 06:12.820
Why doesn't the ECMO group of thoracic surgery come down?

06:12.820 --> 06:15.320
They'll come in a minute.

06:15.320 --> 06:17.890
200 volts, charge it. Step aside.

06:17.890 --> 06:18.890
We are ready.

06:18.890 --> 06:20.530
Let's do this.

06:21.730 --> 06:23.360
Measure the blood pressure.

06:24.000 --> 06:25.560
Make the conversion.

06:26.330 --> 06:27.900
Confirming data.

06:27.900 --> 06:29.070
Where are you going?

06:29.070 --> 06:31.000
Hey, O Su Jeong.

06:29.830 --> 06:31.500
[Diagnosis and Treatment Assistance Center]

06:34.770 --> 06:36.610
Professor Cha Yeong Min,

06:37.310 --> 06:38.810
[EunSang University Medical Center]

06:42.480 --> 06:44.780
now there are patients in the emergency room who need ECPR,

06:43.210 --> 06:45.980
[ECPR, external cardiopulmonary resuscitation]

06:44.780 --> 06:47.050
please come with me.

06:47.820 --> 06:48.990
[O Su Jeong]

06:49.450 --> 06:51.060
Intern O?

06:51.060 --> 06:53.220
I'll do the self introduction later, please come with me.

06:53.220 --> 06:57.230
Sure enough, interns
just like not knowing anything and making troubles everywhere.

06:57.230 --> 06:58.860
It's understandable, I was like this in the past.

06:58.860 --> 07:00.670
It's the privilege of intern.

07:00.670 --> 07:02.330
Professor, mind your back.

07:05.700 --> 07:08.270
I'm sorry, professor, we run out of time.

07:08.270 --> 07:10.070
Hurry, hurry.

07:10.610 --> 07:12.580
What are you doing?

07:19.950 --> 07:21.750
Intern O, let me keep it short.

07:21.750 --> 07:22.450
First,

07:22.450 --> 07:24.190
I don't treat patients casually. Because

07:24.190 --> 07:25.990
I'm not a doctor who sees any patients casually.

07:25.990 --> 07:26.930
Second,

07:26.930 --> 07:28.930
I don't treat the emergency. Because,

07:28.930 --> 07:30.800
it will be a few steps till the patients can reach me.

07:30.800 --> 07:31.400
Third,

07:31.400 --> 07:33.230
I won't treat patients like that. Like what?

07:33.230 --> 07:36.070
Like the one just got in there.

07:38.870 --> 07:42.010
This pair of hands is used for patients with 1% hope of survival.

07:42.010 --> 07:43.810
Professor, behind you.

07:44.310 --> 07:45.880
Damn it.

07:47.180 --> 07:48.380
Professor, if you have this time...

07:48.380 --> 07:50.620
If you have this time?

07:54.420 --> 07:56.890
Intern O, please hurry back to the emergency room.

07:56.890 --> 07:59.790
You need to learn to declare death.

07:59.790 --> 08:03.960
I need to save the ones that should live.

08:11.640 --> 08:13.540
Lunatic.

08:35.059 --> 08:36.690
Name of the patient?

08:38.030 --> 08:39.200
Well...

08:39.200 --> 08:41.200
Name of the patient?

08:41.830 --> 08:45.000
It's Sin Jeong U.

08:49.440 --> 08:54.010
Patient, Sin Jeong U, at 9:31, on September 1,

08:56.010 --> 08:57.750
Died.

09:13.400 --> 09:16.200
What a nasty person.

09:17.070 --> 09:20.840
Who is it? Did you find that person?

09:20.840 --> 09:23.270
Hey, do you know who that is?

09:23.270 --> 09:26.480
Who else can it be? The glamorous gangster doctor.

09:26.480 --> 09:30.050
Gangster? Are you messing things up?

09:30.050 --> 09:35.420
Don't you know that he is a top doctor that the dean dare not to mess up with?

09:32.550 --> 09:35.250
[EunSang University Medical Center]

09:40.960 --> 09:44.700
He performed a single operation during the internship stage,

09:44.700 --> 09:47.600
which saved the emergency patient.

09:47.600 --> 09:51.270
The whole hospital was shocked, and people think it's outrageous.

09:51.270 --> 09:53.440
But there have been similar things a few times before.

09:53.440 --> 09:56.910
Right now, any patient he touches lives.

09:56.910 --> 10:00.880
Rumor says that he's being possessed by a ghost.

10:01.810 --> 10:05.180
What did you say just now?

10:05.180 --> 10:07.950
Which one? He performed a single operation during intern?

10:07.950 --> 10:09.920
You cannot believe that, too, right?

10:09.920 --> 10:11.420
He's the same age like you as intern,

10:11.420 --> 10:13.090
even a genius...

10:13.090 --> 10:17.500
No, the possessed-by-a-ghost thing.

10:17.500 --> 10:21.530
It's just a metaphor, describes the medical skills of being possessed by God.

10:21.530 --> 10:25.240
How can it be a real ghost?

10:28.170 --> 10:30.040
Female, 33 years old. Patient of  Behcet syndrome.

10:29.940 --> 10:31.240
[EunSang University Medical Center]

10:30.040 --> 10:32.780
According to AR, colon ulcer showed inflammation, after three surgeries,

10:32.780 --> 10:38.050
it developed into an aneurysm. Prof. Cha will perform the fourth this afternoon.

10:41.890 --> 10:44.720
[Quadrido: the fourth surgery]

10:41.920 --> 10:42.950
The fourth.

10:42.950 --> 10:46.360
The fourth, not the fifth?

10:46.360 --> 10:48.560
Well, it's the fifth surgery.

10:48.560 --> 10:52.400
Technically, it's a reoperation of the fourth surgery.

10:53.030 --> 10:55.030
Prof. Cha knows that too.

10:55.030 --> 10:56.770
It's a disease that comes back often.

10:56.770 --> 10:58.040
When it happens, you have a surgery.

10:58.040 --> 11:00.770
Over time, the connection becomes severe and there are adhesions everywhere.

11:00.770 --> 11:02.510
The blood vessels in the chest burst.

11:02.510 --> 11:04.880
It's a tricky and difficult surgery.

11:05.740 --> 11:09.280
Why does the section chief do such a difficult surgery?

11:09.280 --> 11:12.780
That's because all the other doctors said they couldn't do it.

11:12.780 --> 11:15.890
Then let the section chief do the reoperation too.

11:19.460 --> 11:20.760
Professor...

11:20.760 --> 11:21.560
What's wrong?

11:21.560 --> 11:24.030
The patient said he didn’t trust the section chief.

11:24.800 --> 11:27.830
He wants to change the surgeon.

11:27.830 --> 11:29.870
Then we have no choice. Prepare for the operation.

11:29.870 --> 11:31.500
Next.

11:37.740 --> 11:39.010
70 year old male patient

11:39.010 --> 11:40.410
with chronic diabetes and hypertension,

11:40.410 --> 11:42.750
and history of stroke two years ago.

11:42.750 --> 11:45.120
Cardiac sarcoma was found

11:45.120 --> 11:48.020
one month ago when examined for breathlessness.

11:45.550 --> 11:48.820
[Cardiac Sarcoma, a type of rarely occurring primary malignancy of the heart]

11:48.020 --> 11:50.050
That's the one I diagnosed and treated.

11:50.050 --> 11:52.520
The son asked if his father could have a surgery.

11:52.520 --> 11:54.790
So, what, are you going to do it?

11:55.930 --> 11:57.100
I can't do it.

11:57.100 --> 11:58.930
How can I do that?

11:58.930 --> 12:00.770
Can Prof. Cha do it?

12:00.770 --> 12:02.430
No, I cannot.

12:02.430 --> 12:03.900
Well, Professor Cha...

12:03.900 --> 12:06.470
Don't just say that and think about it.

12:06.470 --> 12:09.510
And the filial piety of being a son.

12:16.150 --> 12:18.520
A hematoma or tumor powder that falls out of the heart

12:18.520 --> 12:21.620
may go to the brain, causing a higher possibility of a worsening stroke.

12:21.620 --> 12:25.220
There is also the possibility of reoccurrence due to unstable removal despite the hard work.

12:25.220 --> 12:27.660
He can still live one year without a surgery.

12:27.660 --> 12:30.260
If you do not want to shorten the few years of his life barely left,

12:30.260 --> 12:31.630
a filial son

12:31.630 --> 12:33.900
would let him spend the rest of his life in peace.

12:33.900 --> 12:36.300
Tell the son that.

12:36.300 --> 12:38.400
Prof. Cha, don't do this.

12:38.400 --> 12:40.440
Next!

12:48.680 --> 12:50.850
He knew it and he did it to make me look bad.

12:50.850 --> 12:53.480
He treated me, a section chief, like shit.

12:53.480 --> 12:54.820
When young people think they are capable,

12:54.820 --> 12:56.950
they become aggressive and arrogant.

12:56.950 --> 13:00.590
Go on and see what that will lead you to.

13:00.590 --> 13:03.060
Heaven, please don’t just observe out there.

13:03.060 --> 13:06.030
That's right, today's the day.

13:06.030 --> 13:10.130
All right, you young man, meet your opponent.

13:11.440 --> 13:14.270
Relax and be gentle.

13:17.780 --> 13:21.350
You can't say a word in front of people, you have to...

13:21.350 --> 13:23.750
But what does that mean?

13:23.750 --> 13:25.780
What opponent?

13:25.780 --> 13:29.590
OK, it's over. Pull it down.

13:30.590 --> 13:32.720
How many of these are there?

13:33.520 --> 13:35.160
Why has he always been like that?

13:35.160 --> 13:36.460
Like a loose screw.

13:36.460 --> 13:38.560
Today is the day to meet the newcomer.

13:38.560 --> 13:41.330
He's been working so hard on his own, and is so happy

13:41.330 --> 13:43.470
to see a newcomer.

13:43.470 --> 13:45.240
Ah, is it today?

13:45.240 --> 13:47.840
What's he working hard for since we have the Law of Specialist Physicians.

13:47.840 --> 13:49.610
Why hasn't he shown himself yet?

13:49.610 --> 13:50.880
He is absent on the first day.

13:50.880 --> 13:51.980
You'll have to bring him here.

13:51.980 --> 13:54.010
I will.

13:54.010 --> 13:56.410
But what's with the look on your face?

13:56.410 --> 14:00.080
What, are you upset that a patient has been declared dead so early in the morning?

14:00.690 --> 14:02.320
No, I'm not.

14:02.920 --> 14:03.860
But how do you know?

14:03.860 --> 14:05.060
I saw it on the way in.

14:05.060 --> 14:07.160
The patient was in unwitnessed cardiac arrest.

14:05.720 --> 14:09.030
[Unwitnessed arrest: No witnessed cardiac arrest]

14:07.160 --> 14:09.030
He was in the hospital for 30 minutes and didn't respond.

14:09.030 --> 14:11.300
That's the end of it, isn't it?

14:24.210 --> 14:25.240
What about ECMO?

14:25.240 --> 14:26.140
Did not use that.

14:26.140 --> 14:27.450
Well done.

14:27.450 --> 14:28.910
ECMO Priming costs 3 million at a time

14:27.780 --> 14:30.510
[ECMO Priming: ECMO catheter filled with liquid]

14:28.910 --> 14:30.510
It is disposable.

14:30.510 --> 14:33.420
Why waste money when it's useless anyway?

14:33.420 --> 14:35.090
Well done.

14:48.300 --> 14:50.000
You are Professor Cha Yeong Min, right?

14:50.000 --> 14:51.400
I've heard a lot about you.

14:51.400 --> 14:52.940
They say you are the best doctor in our hospital.

14:52.940 --> 14:56.540
Yes, indeed, you are?

14:58.540 --> 15:01.750
You've got the hands of a god.

15:02.380 --> 15:04.150
They're unexpectedly beautiful.

15:04.150 --> 15:06.380
I'm usually good at managing them.

15:06.380 --> 15:09.950
But... who are you?

15:09.950 --> 15:11.990
A president once said

15:11.990 --> 15:14.960
one genius feeds 100,000 people.

15:14.960 --> 15:18.260
Wait a minute.
Our hospital has 2,000 permanent medical staff

15:18.260 --> 15:20.830
and 5,800 general employees, that is about 8,000 in total.

15:20.830 --> 15:24.800
Wow, Professor Cha could feed 10 hospitals!

15:24.800 --> 15:25.400
Oh...

15:25.400 --> 15:28.210
ECMO costs 3 million a time. That's a general employee's salary.

15:28.210 --> 15:32.540
So if you save ten times, you can earn the annual salary of an employee.

15:32.540 --> 15:34.750
What's up?

15:34.750 --> 15:35.780
Who are you?

15:35.780 --> 15:40.250
So eminent, but I have heard that he has a sharp personality.

15:40.250 --> 15:41.390
You're...

15:41.390 --> 15:44.060
That's the personality of a genius, privilege and charm.

15:44.060 --> 15:45.560
Aristotle said

15:45.560 --> 15:48.160
there is no such thing as a genius without a little bit of arrogance.

15:48.160 --> 15:51.930
It takes a whole hospital to cultivate a genius.

15:53.430 --> 15:55.270
After all, he has medical skills of a god.

15:55.270 --> 15:59.540
If you have a problem, you can always come to me.

16:03.310 --> 16:05.080
Hello, bro.

16:15.020 --> 16:17.320
You guys go ahead.

16:17.320 --> 16:21.130
Bro, where's the locker?

16:21.130 --> 16:23.290
It's over there.

16:29.300 --> 16:30.600
That's right.

16:32.040 --> 16:33.970
I will start working with you today.

16:33.970 --> 16:37.880
Doctor Go Seung Tak.

16:38.410 --> 16:40.440
Please take care of me in the future.

16:47.490 --> 16:49.390
Oh, please...

16:52.360 --> 16:54.930
Is that the new guy who's coming today?

16:56.630 --> 16:59.530
Who is he?

16:59.530 --> 17:02.630
Hey, who's that guy?

17:31.060 --> 17:32.900
You know him, don't you?

17:32.900 --> 17:35.930
Since when? Since where?

17:35.930 --> 17:37.000
How much do you know about him?

17:37.000 --> 17:38.570
I knew him from school.

17:38.570 --> 17:41.010
I don't know much, only a little.

17:41.010 --> 17:44.080
Work hard. Did you teach him?

17:44.080 --> 17:46.110
How dare I?

17:46.110 --> 17:48.750
I just gave him some information.

17:49.250 --> 17:52.150
Information? What information?

17:52.150 --> 17:53.350
Information about arrogance?

17:53.350 --> 17:54.720
I am wronged.

17:54.720 --> 17:56.920
I'm the biggest victim.

17:56.920 --> 17:58.890
Go Seung Tak.

17:59.460 --> 18:01.330
You don't mean that "they told me" Go Seung Tak, do you?

18:01.330 --> 18:03.390
Does Dr. I know him too?

18:03.390 --> 18:06.130
I've only heard of him.

18:06.130 --> 18:07.800
He had an interview when he came as an intern.

18:07.800 --> 18:10.270
It's a legend.

18:10.270 --> 18:14.070
We ask superficial questions at the internship interview.

18:13.940 --> 18:15.640
[EunSang University Medical Center]

18:14.070 --> 18:16.010
Why did you become a doctor

18:16.010 --> 18:17.940
I wanted to help suffering patients.

18:17.940 --> 18:20.710
I wanted to save people's lives.

18:20.710 --> 18:23.550
People said superficial things.

18:23.550 --> 18:24.580
Here's what he said:

18:24.580 --> 18:28.720
Grandpa told me to be a doctor, Mom told me to be a doctor.

18:28.720 --> 18:33.260
So, Grandpa is the President of our consortium.

18:33.260 --> 18:35.760
Mum is the Chairman of the Board.

18:34.230 --> 18:36.090
[Qualified]

18:38.160 --> 18:41.330
Why is there a parachute in the 21st century?

18:45.200 --> 18:46.370
21st century what?

18:46.370 --> 18:49.810
What if specialists demonstrate?

18:49.810 --> 18:52.110
What kind of society is this these days? How dare you?

18:52.110 --> 18:52.880
Let's withdraw it.

18:52.880 --> 18:53.910
Number one in the department.

18:53.910 --> 18:55.050
Number one in the internship evaluation.

18:55.050 --> 18:55.910
If this is a parachute,

18:55.910 --> 18:57.150
Prof. Cha is also a parachute.

18:57.150 --> 18:59.320
You helped with the internship scores.

18:59.320 --> 19:02.150
Since when are specialists selected on the basis of their departmental scores?

19:02.150 --> 19:03.890
What about human nature, sense of mission, sense of life?

19:03.890 --> 19:08.030
When did Prof. Cha have such a deep knowledge of the qualifications of a doctor?

19:08.030 --> 19:09.990
If that's the case, then send him to another professor.

19:09.990 --> 19:12.030
I don't like that one.

19:12.030 --> 19:14.530
He doesn't know enough, does he?

19:14.530 --> 19:16.830
You're here, Vice President of Administration.

19:18.500 --> 19:20.340
Since you're related, you should know each other well.

19:20.340 --> 19:22.810
That's not the only thing he lacks.

19:22.810 --> 19:25.310
He is disagreeable and has got no propriety, manners, and humility.

19:25.310 --> 19:27.750
He has so many flaws.

19:27.750 --> 19:30.710
Please take care of him in the future, Professor Cha.

19:30.710 --> 19:35.520
The future of our consortium is in my hands. Think about that.

19:36.790 --> 19:38.160
Didn't I tell you?

19:38.160 --> 19:40.320
Dr. Go is the heir to our hospital.

19:40.320 --> 19:42.990
But President didn’t want to hand it over to him directly. So, he put forward a condition.

19:42.990 --> 19:45.560
It’s kind of a precondition of succession.

19:51.900 --> 19:53.040
It means

19:53.100 --> 19:57.270
that he gets here to take the certificate for inheriting the Group.

20:00.240 --> 20:03.380
How is it going?

20:03.380 --> 20:05.250
You are asking me?

20:05.250 --> 20:06.450
Why the question?

20:06.450 --> 20:07.820
I can’t stand that kind of guy

20:07.820 --> 20:11.360
walking around in front of me.

20:22.670 --> 20:25.170
It smells good.

20:33.810 --> 20:35.910
This is per…

20:38.320 --> 20:41.950
Who wears perfume in the hospital?

20:41.950 --> 20:44.260
How could I send them perfume and let them wear it in the hospital?

20:44.260 --> 20:47.420
I want them to get rid of the smell of disinfectant when dating after work.

20:47.420 --> 20:48.030
It’s the balance of work and life.

20:48.030 --> 20:49.790
Don’t you understand?

20:49.790 --> 20:51.130
You are done showing off your money.

20:51.130 --> 20:52.400
Time to work?

20:52.400 --> 20:55.130
Intern, Go Seung Tak.

20:59.170 --> 21:00.500
What?

21:00.500 --> 21:02.510
No ward inspection?

